    <summary type="html">&lt;div&gt;&lt;div class="admonition admonition-spoilers"&gt;
&lt;p class="admonition-title"&gt;Spoilers!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We're playing &lt;cite&gt;Evernight&lt;/cite&gt;, the Savage Worlds campaing, so if you
haven't played that you might want to skip this entry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="attending"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Attending&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Clockwise round the table, starting with the Games Master:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class="simple"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;T.K.B., the Games Master.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;M.A., playing Jostein, a Human Red Knight.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;T.A., playing Corazon, an Elven Battle Mage; and Dag (who was
almost D.B.'s character), a Human Sun Priest.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;E.A., playing Danyell, an Elven theif.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;No L.B., alas.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="actual-play"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Actual Play&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Played &lt;span class="area"&gt;Act I&lt;/span&gt; through to the beginning of &lt;span class="area"&gt;Scene Six&lt;/span&gt;,
“The Savage Caves”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="section" id="reflections"&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Reflections&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This was a better than average game.  We were able to play an
unusually long session, even though we had to stop for pizza for
dinner in the middle, watching ½ hour of &lt;cite&gt;The Mummy&lt;/cite&gt; while we ate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary>
